headlines.description: — Tyler Herro matched the Miami record with 10 3-pointers and scored a career-high 41 points to help the Heat beat the Houston Rockets 111-108 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro hits 10 3s, scores career-high 41 points for Heat

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 25 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Memphis Grizzlies pounded the Milwaukee Bucks 142-101 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has triple-double as Grizzlies trounce Bucks 142-101

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored a season-high 39 points and had eight rebounds in the Utah Jazz’s 132-129 overtime victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson scores 39 points, Jazz outlast Pelicans in OT

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored 27 points, Chris Paul added 15 points and 13 assists and the Phoenix Suns snapped a five-game losing streak with a 111-95 victory over the depleted Los Angeles Clippers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns snap 5-game skid with 111-95 win over depleted Clippers
